The Chronicle   Lizzy Nekhoma, Chronicle Reporter THE family of South African rapper Costa Tich (28) who died after collapsing on stage while performing on 11 March 2023 has issued a statement thanking fans for supporting his career. The actual cause of his death is yet to be determined, but according to rumors, Costa-born Costantinos Tsobanoglou- reportedly had a history of epilepsy, a brain disorder that causes seizures. Below is  the full statement  from his family: <img class="alignnone wp-image-688708 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/03/Untitled-1-14.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/03/Untitled-1-14.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/03/Untitled-1-14-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> More to follow…